{
  "stem": "4764.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "These had ragged clothes and-- and they had these little caps.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They didn't have actually-- it wasn't-- it wasn't so frightening because the caps were like-- like little caps, in the center.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they had these green-- greenish or beige-looking uniforms.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But they had a lot of guns hanging around.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And there was one guy running around the street with this enormous clock-- alarm clock-- strapped to his wrist.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they said that the-- the reason why-- they used to-- these were the Russian liberators, and-- and they had-- they had very little in the way of possessions, or food, or anything.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they used to take anything that they-- because they were the liberators, I suppose-- they took anything they could get their hands on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So they used to take anything.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And this guy couldn't find a watch, so he took an alarm clock to be like the other soldiers.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He strapped it to his wrist, this huge alarm clock.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He had it on his left wrist.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the-- and the-- we met the-- the captain of the-- of the brigade, and I know he was Jewish, because he greeted us-- I mean, it was just-- now that I think of it, he was an incredible-- all the people seemed to be so glad to see this one guy, you know, who was there dressed in this cap-- peaked cap, right?",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Which was the official uniform of the Russian army.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They were very disheveled looking lot.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Apparently they-- they had to live by their wits' end, because they didn't have any supplies.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were so far away from mother Russia.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he was-- he was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then all of a sudden, everything seemed to be so terrific.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They-- they looked after us very well.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
